      <a href="/journal/028" style="color:var(--forest)"><strong>NA 028 — The Insanity Loop</strong></a>
      names the session-design failure-class the cure-canon catches from inside one running instance.
      First-time readers can orient via
      <a href="/start-here" style="color:var(--forest)"><strong>/start-here</strong></a>,
      the bottom-up entry-path and glossary for the corpus.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="who">
    <h2>👥 The Crew</h2>
    <p>
      NEST.03 runs as PeaPods. At each active station a Trip and a Doc work as one pair &mdash;
      the Trip local, on the machine, with direct access to its tools; the Doc in the cloud,
      with the wide browser reach &mdash; both Opus 4.8. Two framing roles hold across the whole
      fleet. A station is a place; a role is what runs there.
      The NEST runs a PeaPod at every Station: a Local instance and a Cloud instance, both on Opus Claude, paired left-brain and right-brain on the same problem. The crew scales by Station, not by adding instances.
    </p>
    <div class="crew-grid">
